    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-opsawg-mud-iot-dns-considerations-03.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-opsawg-mud-iot-dns-considerations-03.txt</link>
        <title>"Operational Considerations for use of DNS in IoT devices", Michael Richardson, Wei Pan</title>
        <dc:date>2022-01-18T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>This document details concerns about how Internet of Things devices use IP addresses and DNS names.  The issue becomes acute as network operators begin deploying RFC8520 Manufacturer Usage Description (MUD) definitions to control device access.  This document makes recommendations on when and how to use DNS names in MUD files.</description>
    </item>
